Investor mindset seeing it as:  Whatever is not appreciated is depreciated and eventually lost. This is a key principle in investing.  Just think about it.  Butterflies are beautiful shiny objects - brand new car, designs handbag you latest IPhone you buy every year. The  moment you drive or walk out the shop, your new dearest belonging starts to depreciate and start losing its value. And if you appear in cycle of neediness for upgrade, you literally flashing your money down the drain. There is nothing wrong with that, if you want to live in the moment. But do you really believe that you will be able to sustain your imagery lifestyle rest of your life, especially in retirement?  On the other hand, when you spend your time making a beautiful garden and at first you start building your investment property portfolio , you building the foundation to your lifestyle and all above comes with it!  #investing #investormindset #womenmindset #friday #fridaythoughts

Stop making this huge mistake.  It could cost you money or even whole your financial future. Holiday season is in full swing. BBQs, Christmas parties and family gatherings are filling our diaries.  And these great gatherings can be also a time when you could make the biggest mistake in your investment property decisions.  It seems that our family and friends are experts in many areas, especially when it comes to property. The opinions suddenly become great advice, even the truth is, that possibly, none of them built a successful property portfolio themselves.  And even if they have built their own portfolio, their goals and circumstances wouldn’t be the same as yours. So, how do you know that their property advice is going to be right for you? I often find, the most opinionated people who call themselves experts are only listening to media and making the assumption from 7 o’clock news.  I understand, It is satisfying  to feel supported by those close to us. But when it comes to investment property advice, it might be better left to the professionals in most cases.  Because, often the price for wrong advice can be huge. It can cost you hundreds of thousands of dollars in future.  I’m not saying every opinion is bad opinion, but when you listen to them, do your own research fully afterwards, and seek the advice of experts, who works in industry day in day out.  Remember, just because you trust your family and friends, it doesn’t mean they always have experience and expertise. After-all, don’t let them or anyone else crash your property investment dreams before you even get started. #investormindset #mindset #reallifequotes #womenmindset #investmentstrategy #propertyportfolio #womeninvestors #womeninvestors
Don't keep these words only in your device, take these into the real-life by investing into your future!  #investormindset #mindset #mindsetmotivation #reallifequotes #womenmindset

Fail To Plan, You Plan To Fail.  This determines which statistics you could be part of:  In Australia, just over 70% of investors hold only 1 investment property.  Vs  Approximately 1% of property investors hold 6 or more investment properties  That’s why, Developing the right STRATEGY and SYSTEM is second ingredient in our property portfolio recipe.  Any property investment should be part of wider financial plan that takes in your current position, and where you hope to go, within a specific timeframe. Whether you are investing in property for your retirement, investing to leave a legacy for your children or simply looking to complement other assets, it’s important to know and align property investing with your goals, personal needs and your big  dreams. Once you know your vision and your why, the property investment strategy will plan for that accordingly, factoring in things like your appetite for risk and your current situation. Remember, It’s all about you, no one size fits all!  #investmentstrategy #propertyportfolio #women #womeninvestors #womeninvestorsnetwork #investorsmindset #moneymindset #australianwomen@Liberty Property Strategies

Let’s bake the cake!  Today”s ingredient is: Developing the right investor MINDSET  As we mention in my previous post - Building healthy property portfolio, that will eventually free your time to do more of what you love is based on a specific process, the recipe with four critical ingredients   In my eyes this is the most important ingredient that will determine whether you walk into fast lane, star  and succeed or stay in your dream land.  I understand, just talking about investing,, especially property investing can feel complexed and intimidating topic to you. But really, it doesn’t have to be this way. Firstly, let’s be straight, the road to becoming financially free is long, property investing is long term game. And yes, it requires you to take risks.  True is, you  can’t save your way to wealth.  It’s such a common belief money in saving account is a safe option and many people don”t realise money in  saving account losing value over time due to inflation.  Saving account definitely has an own place for goals such as saving for investment deposit and emergency fund. But your mindset needs to grow way above.  That”s why start developing habits such as reading, listening podcasts on topics to expose yourself to the perspectives, opinions, and learnings from others, rather than just from media.  Visualise regularly about how you would like to be, and your behavior will slowly follow. Find your true why and purpose why you want to invest, because word Money is only shallow shiny object that won’t get you there.  These types of habits will start exercise your mind and build the energy that will  drive you forward and make you self-reliant. original_post.description: Changing your habits regarding how you perceive money is crucial. Regardless of your income, maintaining a consumer/spender mindset can lead to financial strain. Accumulating wealth isn’t just about having funds to spend—it’s about adopting a saver/investor mentality. Additional requirements for Capital Gain Tax (CGT) exemption; you have to live in the property for more than 12 months and not using it for business purposes. On the other side, you can get a 50 % CGT discount by owning the property for at least 12 months and not claiming it as your main residence. This discount will go toward how much capital gain that will be taxed. For example, your CGT is $250K. If you get the discount, then your CGT is $125K and this $125K will be taxed instead of the $250K. There are also a few exemptions that are eligible for the discount; you were a temporary resident of Australia when you owned the asset, a beneficiary of a trust that owned the asset, and used the asset for business purposes. However, to ensure that you’re 100% eligible for CGT exemption or 50% discount, consult with a good tax advisor so you can get great return on investment. *not financial or legal advice. This post has been widely popular. Please speak to your accountant for advice. As a content creator I am here to spread awareness and share information based on my personal experience and my dealing with real estate investors. Tax is a complex system, and you need a good tax adviser if you are serious about investing.  All the best. . #property #propertyinvesting #propertyinvestor #taxadvice  #investingtips

Your home can create tax-free income ↓ Equity is the difference between the market value of your property and the outstanding loan in the property. For example, your property market value is $500,000 and the outstanding loan is $300,000. The equity of the property would be $200,000. You can tap into this equity to gain the tax-free money ($200,000) to invest in another property. You can do this by refinancing the property or having another mortgage on top of the first mortgage. The interest on the loan that you took through the equity withdrawal is tax deductible as long as it is for investment purposes.  *not financial or legal advice . . . #equity #realestateinvestments #taxdeductions #personalwealth #taxfree #taxfreeincome #taxaustralia #propertyinvesting #propertyinvestment #realestate #realestateaustralia

original_post.description: Wir haben oft gehört: "Wenn du große Ziele erreichen willst, musst du anfangen wie ein Investor zu denken". Aber was bedeutet das eigentlich? Ein Investor denkt strategisch. Sie planen für die langfristige, eine Vision, die über den nächsten Monat oder das nächste Jahr hinausgeht. Sie treffen Entscheidungen basierend auf Forschung, Analyse und sorgfältiger Betrachtung der Risiken und Vorteile. Ein Investor ist bereit, jetzt zu investieren (in Zeit, Geld, Ressourcen oder Anstrengung) für zukünftige Renditen. Sie wissen, dass große Erfolge nicht über Nacht passieren, sondern dass sie Zeit und kontinuierliche Anstrengung erfordern. Ein Investor bleibt auch in Zeiten der Herausforderung engagiert. Sie lassen sich nicht von kurzfristigen Ausfällen oder Rückschlägen entmutigen, sondern sehen sie als Lernmöglichkeiten und Anpassungspunkte. Sie wissen, dass das Scheitern Teil des Prozesses ist und dass die größten Siege oft aus den größten Herausforderungen hervorgehen. Ganz gleich, ob du ein Unternehmer bist, ein Profi, der in deinem Fachgebiet vorankommen möchte, oder jemand, der an persönlichem Wachstum und Entwicklung interessiert ist, die Denkweise eines Investors kann dir helfen, große Ziele zu erreichen. Investiere in dich selbst, in deine Fähigkeiten und Kenntnisse, und sei bereit, die nötige Zeit und Energie aufzubringen. Denken wie ein Investor bedeutet letztendlich, das große Bild zu sehen, Geduld zu üben und auf die langfristigen Vorteile hinzuarbeiten. Mit dieser Denkweise kannst du nicht nur große Ziele erreichen, sondern auch einen bedeutenden Einfluss haben. #InvestorMindset #GroßeZiele #PersönlichesWachstum #LangfristigeDenkweise #InvestiereinDichSelbst Zum Video mit Philip https://held.tips/mi8c

Zypern ist nicht nur für seine malerischen Strände und das sonnige Wetter bekannt, sondern auch für seine attraktiven Steuervorteile. Das kleine Inselstaat im östlichen Mittelmeer bietet sowohl Privatpersonen als auch Unternehmen lukrative Anreize, um ihren Wohnsitz oder ihre Geschäftstätigkeit nach Zypern zu verlagern. Einer der Hauptvorteile ist die Möglichkeit eines einfachen Umzugs bei geringer Aufenthaltsdauer. Zypern hat ein besonderes Steuersystem namens "Non-Domicile", das es Einzelpersonen ermöglicht, von zahlreichen Steuervorteilen zu profitieren. Gemäß diesem System müssen Personen, die ihren Wohnsitz nach Zypern verlegen, nur auf ihr Einkommen besteuert werden, das aus zyprischen Quellen stammt, während ihr ausländisches Einkommen von der Besteuerung befreit ist. Dies gilt für einen Zeitraum von 17 Jahren, vorausgesetzt, dass bestimmte Bedingungen erfüllt sind. Eine der Hauptbedingungen für dieses Steuersystem ist eine Begrenzung der Aufenthaltsdauer in Zypern. Personen, die von den Steuervorteilen profitieren möchten, müssen weniger als 183 Tage pro Jahr auf der Insel verbringen. Dies ermöglicht es Steuerzahlern, in Zypern ansässig zu werden und dennoch ihre Geschäfte im Ausland fortzuführen, ohne ihr Einkommen in Zypern zu versteuern. Darüber hinaus bietet Zypern attraktive Steuervorteile für Unternehmen. Der Unternehmenssteuersatz beträgt nur 12,5 %, einer der niedrigsten in der Europäischen Union. Unternehmen, die in Zypern ansässig sind, können von einer Reihe weiterer Steuervorteile profitieren, wie zum Beispiel Steuerbefreiungen für Dividendeneinkommen, Kapitalgewinne und Tochterunternehmen. Ein weiterer Anreiz für den Umzug nach Zypern ist die Möglichkeit, ein Teil eines EU-Landes zu sein. Dies ermöglicht es Personen und Unternehmen, von den zahlreichen Vorteilen der EU-Mitgliedschaft zu profitieren #zypern #auswandern #auswanderung #steuern #steuernsparen #steuersystem #steuervorteil #nextlevelshit #nls zum Video im ersten Kommentarfeld

Geniale Gedanken und pure Verrücktheit - sie könnten nicht unterschiedlicher sein, aber gleichzeitig haben sie erstaunlich viel gemeinsam. Beide können unerwartet auftreten und uns mit offenem Mund und erstauntem Gesicht zurücklassen. Beide können in Form von unkonventionellem Denken, wilden Ideen und nicht alltäglichen Konzepten auftreten. Doch der entscheidende Unterschied kann gefunden werden, wenn man genauer hinblickt. Geniale Gedanken sind üblicherweise das Resultat tiefer Reflexion, kreativer Prozesse und einem Verständnis, das über das offensichtliche hinaus geht. Es sind Ideen und Konzepte, die auf der Grundlage von Logik, Vernunft und einer gezielten Kreativität stehen. Sie sind inspirierend und können unsere Sicht auf die Dinge verändern, sie erweitern uns und treiben uns in neue Richtungen der Entwicklung voran. Auf der anderen Seite kann pure Verrücktheit oft irrational sein, fehlende Logik aufweisen und keinen klar erkennbaren Zweck verfolgen. Verrücktheit könnte eine spontane Obsession sein, etwas, das zwar interessant sein kann, aber oft nicht zu konstruktiven Ergebnissen führt. Der entscheidende Unterschied liegt also in der Anwendung und den Ergebnissen. Ein genialer Gedanke hat das Potenzial, die Welt zu verbessern, eine neue Perspektive einzuführen oder eine effiziente Lösung anzubieten. Pure Verrücktheit hingegen, obwohl sie oft faszinierend und unterhaltsam ist, führt selten zu einem Nutzen für ihre Umgebung. Interessant ist aber, dass in der Geschichte oft der schmale Grat zwischen Genie und Verrücktheit durchschritten wurde. Viele der größten Denker der Menschheit wurden zu ihrer Zeit als verrückt angesehen, ihre Ideen als absurd und ihre Methoden als unorthodox. Es scheint also, dass ein gewisses Maß an "Verrücktheit" notwendig sein könnte, um die Grenzen des Denkens wirklich zu verschieben und echte Genialität zu erreichen. ##kreativesDenken #genie #verrückt #geldhelden zum Video mit Egon https://held.tips/nhxe

Durch Bereitstellung von hochwertigen Inhalten können Sie Ihr Publikum informieren, erziehen oder unterhalten. Es geht darum, einen Mehrwert zu bieten und dadurch eine treue Anhängerschaft aufzubauen. 2️⃣ Social Media bleibt ein entscheidendes Werkzeug und bietet uns unzählige Möglichkeiten, Öffentlichkeit zu erzeugen. Die Macht der sozialen Netzwerke sollte nicht unterschätzt werden, egal ob Facebook, Instagram, LinkedIn oder TikTok - diese Plattformen ermöglichen es uns auf vielfältige Weise, Menschen zu erreichen. 3️⃣ Influencer Marketing ist eine weitere wachsende Strategie. Dabei handelt es sich um die Zusammenarbeit mit einflussreichen Personen in Social Media, die Ihrer Marke helfen können, Glaubwürdigkeit und Bekanntheit zu erlangen. 4️⃣ Storytelling ist ein wirksames Instrument um menschliche Verbindungen zu schaffen. Menschen lieben Geschichten - sie sind tiefer, emotionaler und berührender als bloße Fakten. Nutzen Sie daher Storytelling, um Ihre Marke zum Leben zu erwecken und eine stärkere Beziehung zu Ihrem Publikum aufzubauen. 5️⃣ Last but not least, ist es wichtig, die Macht des persönlichen Kontakts nicht zu unterschätzen. Nichts ersetzt das menschliche Gesicht hinter einer Marke oder einer Botschaft. Jeder dieser Ansätze hat seine eigenen Vorteile und Herausforderungen. Es liegt an Ihnen, herauszufinden, welche Strategie am besten zu Ihnen und Ihrer Mission passt. Bleiben Sie flexibel, bleiben Sie. zum Video mit Patrick https://held.tips/ngjs

Egal ob Sie es Glück nennen oder einen Trick, es ist nicht zu leugnen, dass die Reichen einige Geheimnisse für ihren Erfolg haben. Eine besondere Strategie, Netzwerke, harte Arbeit oder einfach nur eine andere Denkweise können eine große Rolle dabei spielen, wie Reichtum generiert und erhalten wird. Eines der größten "Geheimnisse" der Reichen ist definitiv der Vermögensaufbau. Anstatt ihr Geld für Verschwendung auszugeben, investieren sie in Aktien, Immobilien oder andere wachsende Unternehmungen. Und während wir oft Bilder von luxuriösen Lebensstilen sehen, kann das wahre Geheimnis des Reichtums tatsächlich darin bestehen, bescheiden zu leben und zu vermeiden, Geld auszugeben, nur um zu prahlen. Ein weiteres gemeinsames Merkmal der Reichen ist, dass sie mehrere Einkommensströme haben. Sie sind nicht nur auf einen Gehaltsscheck angewiesen, sondern können auf Investitionen, Mieten und andere Quellen zählen, um kontinuierliches Einkommen zu generieren. Werden diese Strategien des Erfolgs auch Sie reich machen? Es gibt keine Garantie. Aber eines ist sicher: Erfolg kommt nicht einfach durch Glück. Es kommt durch Planung, harte Arbeit und Geduld. Und wenn wir diese Geheimnisse zu unserem Vorteil nutzen können, stehen die Chancen gut, dass auch wir unsere finanziellen Ziele erreichen werden. #ReichtumGeheimnisse #FinanziellerErfolg Zur Eichhörnchenstrategie https://held.tips/nezt

These are the 3 money tips I give to others as a self-made millionaire and former California public school math teacher. 1. Stop buying stupid things that are going to depreciate in value over time. Don’t try to impress friends with your material goods. And if you have friends who place more value on these things, it’s a good time to reevaluate your friend circle. 2. Don’t rely on just one income stream. You must have passive income streams or you will work forever. The easiest way to start is to open a high-yields savings with any of the below: 	@wealthfront 	@capitalone 	@ally 	@apple 	@Marcus 	 If you want to start investing, here are the 4 steps to start: (1) choose a brokerage company, (2) open an account like a Roth IRA, (3) set up recurring deposits, and (4) buy assets, preferably something that tracks the S&P500 and DOW30. I’ll go over this next Tuesday at 5:30PM PT if you want to ask me questions. 3. Stop following finance gurus and these get-rich-quick schemes. No AMC, GME, BBBY, marijuana stocks, useless cryptocurrencies, or whatever is in hype. The fastest way to build your wealth is to be the turtle. I hope this helps give you a little motivation to start building wealth today. How “Passive” are Rental Properties?  Not as passive as most #realestategurus want you to believe.  Your cash flow depends heavily on … 1️⃣ The type of property you’re buying ex. single-family vs multifamily  2️⃣ The way you’re operating your rental — property management, maintenance, repairs, requests, etc.  Section 8 is a profitable way to offer affordable, lower end housing …  Only if you’re willing to do all the very “active” legwork like the landlord application, inspections, and training. That’s ON TOP of the work you need to do for the property management.  An experienced #realestateinvestor understands the work it takes to run highly-profitable rental properties. That’s why so many investors are choosing to expand their portfolios through #realestatesyndication.  Syndication allows you to put your money towards a #propertyinvestment, receive returns, and get all the benefits of ownership without the hassle.  That’s real estate investing in a truly passive way.  Comment ‘PASSIVE’ if you’d like to learn more our investment opportunities. 🚗💥 Turning Lemons into Cash! 💰 Let me take you back to the day I had my dad check out this F-150. 🚙 The back latch was stuck, the windows refused to budge—basically, it was a hot mess! 😅 But, it started, so my dad, being the practical guy he is, said, "Worth $500, son." I thought, "Alright, here you go!" Now, picture this: Dad driving that clunker home in July heat, no AC, stopping traffic on Route 3 or wherever. 😓 Fast forward to the next day, I take it for a spin, and BAM—purple liquid waterfall the moment I touch the stick shift. 😱 Dad's verdict? Pretty much a death sentence. But, in the world of real estate, where challenges are just opportunities in disguise, I decided to market the heck out of it! 💪 Got a tow truck company to swoop in and pay me $550 for that not-so-glamorous F-150. BOOM! 💥 Yeah, baby! 🎉 Lesson learned: In real estate, even a lemon of a truck can turn into sweet cash with a bit of creativity! 🍋💰 #RealEstateHustle #FromClunkerToCash #EntrepreneurLife 🏡✨ #IgnitionCommunity #RealEstateSuccess #LifeTransformation  https://www.facebook.com/groups/613414509346025

original_post.description: 🏡💰📈 PAY your mortgage off FAST and PAY less interest!! Because Mortgages use an amortization schedule, adding additional principal each month, or in a lump sum does not just pay your loan quicker, it skips interest payments. It advances the payment down the schedule, so if you pay an extra payment on payment 10 and the principal is enough to cover the next five payments. The next one you pay will be payment number 15 and you pay zero interest on the payments you skipped, it is a powerful tool. If you make one extra payment per year, in most cases, you can chop seven years off of a standard 30 year loan. #passiveincomestream #financialplanner #investment #rentalincome #moneymanagement #roi #returnoninvestment #wealthmanagement #financial #cashflowquadrant #rentalproperty #realtor #financegoals #businessplanning #entrepreneur #propertyinvestors #businessgrowth#entrepreneurs #financialtips #financialeducation #businesscoach #fliphouses #financiallyfree #businessstrategy #investormindset#stockmarketinvesting #stockmarket #wealthbuilders #realestateblog #realestateagent

original_post.description: ⭕️Hindsight is always 2020. In my almost 13 years in #realestate, I continue hearing the “I WISH I WOULD HAVE…” sentiments. Make the decision you think is best, but here are my 2 🪙’s… ➡️ I don’t think hoping 🤞🏾& waiting ⏳for 3% interest rates (was not normal) or home prices to decrease 📉 is the wisest strategy (values appreciate over time), but best of luck 🤷🏽‍♀️. And let’s say one or both of those things do happen, the competition between traditional homebuyers & investors will be insane 😵‍💫. While no one has a crystal ball 🔮, I’m reading the room and I firmly believe it will continue to become harder to #achievehomeownership as time goes on. Investors anticipate this, hence the increase in new construction subdivisions solely for lease. Those with an #investormindset (including #traditionalhomebuyers) don’t operate in fear. They think big picture & long-term. They are PROACTIVE and prepare for the opportunity. Their opportunity being the REACTIVE people who don’t have any other option, but to continue renting.

original_post.description: Building confidence in deal-making is all about celebrating small victories. How do we ensure every student feels victorious? We kept it simple and achievable, setting them one task per day. It may have taken 15 to 30 minutes, but it was a win. It's about creating a habit, just like stepping into a gym. Even if you don't work out, you're still an athlete. Inspired by the book 'Atomic Habits', we focused on identity building. In our case, becoming an investor. Investors make X number of calls a day. Instead of obsessing over the end goal, concentrate on daily habits. These small actions will naturally lead to achieving your goal. #BuildingConfidence #SmallVictories #HabitForming #InvestorMindset

posts_info.description: Embrace your dreams often. Don't be a stranger to your own aspirations. If you don't know your dreams, you'll live and die as a stranger to them. We need to identify our dreams. What are our life goals? What do we aim to achieve? What do we want to conquer in life and what do we aspire to be or have? We need to familiarize ourselves with these dreams and make a habit of touching them often. Let's take an example, we want to own our office. Although we have a wonderful rented space where our franchise owners and visitors can experience our culture, we dream of owning a beautiful building. If we don't familiarize ourselves with this dream of owning a building, it will remain just that - a dream. So to each one of you, I hope not only do you dream, but also take time to touch those dreams, understand them, feel them and make them your reality. #TouchYourDreams #KnowYourDreams #LifeGoals #MakeDreamsReality

Why not ask yourself, "why is my body so amazing?" Your mind will find evidence supporting that idea. Like how you were able to carry 500 pounds for a mile. That's seriously impressive. Few people can boast such a feat. You did that, and it's proof that your body is indeed amazing. Your mind is your advocate, gathering evidence to build your confidence. When you ask a bold question, you're not just making a statement - you're challenging your brain to provide evidence. Imagine it like this: You're sitting at a restaurant, five tables away from someone who shouts, "Josh!" Even though they're not calling you, your brain picks up on it. It's always alert, always picking up on details you might not consciously notice. ➡️Follow for more: @codyhofhine ➡️Follow for more:  #MindOverMatter #BodyConfidence #PositiveThinking #MentalStrength

Unveiling the technique of "Lofty Questions". Affirmations aren't as effective as you think. This idea is not new, even in the 1980s, Jose Silva, a pioneer in mind science, claimed that affirmations often fail. Rather, we should trick our subconscious mind into accepting the identity we assign it. This is done by asking questions like, "Why is my body so fantastic?" or "Why am I so kind to everyone?" Affirmations fail because they can't reinforce a belief that isn't genuine. So, if you're doubting your own affirmation, your body is unlikely to accept it. Doesn't matter how many times you affirm you're fit to a body that doesn't believe it, it's just going to dismiss it. #LoftyQuestions #MindOverMatter #PowerOfSubconscious #BelieveInYourself

Waiting for lower interest rates may not be the smartest move in real estate investing... The interest rate is just one piece of the puzzle! Think about this: getting a $500,000 property in today's market, even with slightly higher interest rates, could bring in significant profits...  A year later, the property might be worth $100,000 more! And the interest rate won't even matter! 😉 Honestly, comparing mortgage payments now and waiting for potential rate drops shows little difference at the end of the day.  So, the key is to make the most of the current market rather than trying to predict future changes. posts_info.description: Three ways to we add value on your next BRRRR deal Optimize existing space for functionality Add square footage Add bedrooms  I deep dive into how we do it with a deal that we’re going to close in about a month. . . . . . #brrrrstrategy #realestateinvesting #duediligence #pittsburghrealestate #pittsburgh #realestate101 #biggerpockets #brrrr #multifamilyrealestate #multifamily #multifamilylinvesting

Why do I invest in real estate? At first it was for me to make sure I would never have to worry about my finances. Then it was to provide for my future wife. Now, It’s to create a business that can impact my future wife, future generations and all of our partners. Just as my why has expanded to others, so has my desire to build something greater. That’s the power of real estate.  Anyone can put in the work and create of life of their dreams. And you can do it starting now!

Why do I invest in Multifamily versus Single Family in real estate?  Well, I asked myself the question, am I hunting field mice or antelope?  I chose the path of focusing on multifamily because I thought that it would get me to my financial goals sooner. It can be scaled faster, it’s more efficient from a  management perspective, and it’s valued based on its’ performance and not other comps in the area so I can directly impact my net worth. I would rather give up the instant dopamine hits of closing little mice (single family) for a few months to  get a larger building. This works for me because of my financial freedom goals, available time and investment thesis alignment. It might not be the right path for you. Interested in learning more? Check out the link to my YouTube videos on my bio! . . . . . #brrrrstrategy #realestateinvesting #duediligence #pittsburghrealestate #pittsburgh #realestate101 #biggerpockets #brrrr #multifamilyrealestate #multifamily #multifamilylinvesting

House hacking is the ultimate way to get into real estate if you are just starting. It allows you to purchase a property with little money out of pocket, learn the ropes of managing a property, renovations, and residents. There are powerful tax benefits to it and you can live for less, nearly free, or completely free so you can save money up for your next purchase.  You can buy up to a four unit apartment building so you can start early to build cash flow and equity. It works in any market, with any type of lifestyle.  This is what I did and have been living in for the past year and a half and it has been the foundation of our real estate investing business. . . . . . #brrrrstrategy #realestateinvesting #duediligence #pittsburghrealestate #pittsburgh #realestate101 #biggerpockets #brrrr #multifamilyrealestate #multifamily #multifamilylinvesting #househacking101

original_post.description: There’s a lot of money to be made in real estate so you’re looking to get in the game. Many investors take a slow and steady approach to turning a profit, but that’s not what you have in mind. Instead, you’d like to cash in relatively fast, which is entirely possible. Here are four ways you can make income investing in real estate  📌Wholesaling  To get started, she said you’ll search for distressed sellers who are facing situations like foreclosure or an unwanted property inheritance. Once you find a property, you negotiate a contract to purchase it at a favorable price –typically at 70% after repair value,. Instead of buying the property yourself, you find another investor who is interested in the deal and assign them the contract for the property. 📌Flipping Houses This involves purchasing a property, renovating it and then selling it for a profit.  The key is to identify properties that can be purchased below market value, but have the potential to be turned into a profitable property with some renovation work. Successful house flippers must have an eye for detail, ability to manage a budget and a good sense of the local real estate market. 📌 Short-Term Rentals If you own a property in a desirable location — such as a vacation destination — short-term rentals can be a great way to make money in real estate. “Platforms like Airbnb, VRBO and HomeAway allow you to rent out your property for short-term stays. 📌 Real Estate Investment Trust (REIT) A REIT is a way to invest in real estate without actually owning property,. A REIT is a corporation that owns or finances income-producing real estate. In this type of arrangement, investors purchase shares in the REIT and receive a portion of the income, typically through dividends. Of course, as with anything in business, before making a move, it’s always important to carefully research any potential real estate transactions. The last thing you want is to end up losing money, when you were planning to turn a profit.   Takiyah Coleman, Licensed REALTOR ®️ J. I fell victim to this. It delayed me for months and months. 😓 I was soooo worried about setting up my business, creating an LLC, coming up with a name for my company, that I put all my effort into that rather than looking for deals. BIG MISTAKE… 🤦‍♂️ An LLC is meant to create liability protection and also structure if you partner up with someone. If you are a sole proprietor with nothing to protect yet, why are you so worried about an LLC? The better option, imo, put your energy into finding your first deal. Throw an umbrella insurance policy over it and then worry about the LLC once you need asset protection. ☂️ Some may argue that you should set up an LLC right way. If you want to go that route, be my guest, but don’t let it take away from what really matters. 🚀 As another piece of info, you can always deed a property in your own personal name into an LLC at a later point. Be aware, there is something called a “due on sale” clause that could trigger the bank to force you to pay off the loan. I’ve heard everyone talk about it, I don’t know anyone that’s actually had this happen to them as long as you are paying your mortgage. 🏡💼 This is a debatable topic with pros and cons on both sides. Let me know your thoughts down below and be sure to share this with someone starting their journey. 👇 . Tools I’ve created and use as an investor are in my bio! 🔧💼 . . . #investingforwealth #newinvestor #realestateinvestor #investormindset #buildyournetworth 📈💰

Are you Looking to really diversify your portfolio? We should talk about REITS and CEFs REITs are corporations or trusts that use the pooled capital of many investors to purchase and manage income property and/or mortgage loans. REITs can be a game-changer in your investment portfolio. With lower initial capital requirements, high dividends, and diversification benefits. REITs are traded on NGX just like stocks; you can buy or sell REITs through your stockbroker as with other types of shares. It offers tax advantages to investors and provide a liquid way to invest in real estate, which is an otherwise illiquid market. It also allows investors to share in non-residential properties like hotels, malls, and industrial properties. posts_info.description: DO I BUY REAL ESTATE WITH MY OWN CASH? “Listen up, folks! So, you might be wondering, as a decamillionaire, do I go out there and buy real estate with cold, hard cash right from my pocket? Well, the answer is a big NO. I still believe in using financing, and here’s why. You see, all my wealth is tied up in real estate, and while I’ve got a ton of it, sometimes I do sell a property or two. When I do that, I take that equity and turn it into cash. And you know what I do with that cash? I use it as the down payment for even more real estate deals. It’s like a money-multiplying strategy that keeps growing my wealth.” Subscribe to my account @natalia.zackhaim to find out how you can make money in the American real estate market📈

How do I intend to pass my life lessons and values onto my children? Naturally, I have a deep interest in sharing my strategies with my children, and I approach this matter with utmost seriousness. I fostered a relationship with my children that was built on respect for their understanding and maturity. I took the time to explain my actions and decisions, involving them in various aspects of my work. We attended negotiations together, visited properties, and witnessed the intricacies of rent collection and tenant relations. All of these experiences were seamlessly integrated into our family life, shaping their understanding of business and life itself.

HOW TO START IN REAL ESTATE WITHOUT MONEY?  To kickstart your journey in real estate without waiting for years to accumulate savings, here's a strategic approach:   1️⃣Educate Yourself: Begin by gaining a deep understanding of how the real estate market operates. Knowledge is your foundation.   2️⃣Determine Borrowing Potential: Explore your borrowing options. You can seek financing from hard money lenders, banks, or financial groups. To assess your eligibility and potential funding amount, initiate conversations with these institutions.   3️⃣Calculate Down Payment: Understand the size of the down payment required for your desired real estate investment. This becomes your specific financial target.   4️⃣Reduce Down Payment: Once you have a clear target, focus on ways to minimize your down payment. Explore alternative solutions if you don't want to spend years accumulating savings.   Follow my page @natalia.zackhaim to find out how you can make money in the American real estate market📈

HOW AM I BALANCING BETWEEN FAMILY AND BUSINESS? Well, let me tell you, managing the juggle between family life and being a savvy entrepreneur was no piece of cake. You see, I may not call it “business” per se, but I was deep into the world of entrepreneurship, trying out different things and making my mark. But here’s the kicker – I had my little kiddos to look after. It was a really difficult time, let me tell you. Real estate became more than just an investment; it became a part of my life. I was busy raising children, and in the midst of it all, I was keeping an eye on the real estate game. Picture this: I was doing a ton of work from home, hunched over the computer, crunching numbers, calculating, calculating, calculating. I was sleeping with the idea of real estate, waking up nursing that idea, and reading books while nursing my little ones. I was even multitasking while cooking up a storm in the kitchen – listening to audio gems on real estate while taking care of my precious munchkins. That’s how I seamlessly integrated my life and my real estate entrepreneurship journey, and let me tell you, it was one heck of a ride! #FamilyAndHustle #RealEstateLife #EntrepreneurshipJourney #MultitaskingMama #BalancingAct #NeverStopLearning #NurturingDreams #RaisingFutureMillionaires #RealEstateInvestor #Mompreneur

WHAT COULD BE THE LEVERAGE? Let me break it down for you, my friends. Real estate is like the fortress that can’t be moved, can’t be swiped from under you, not from the bank either. You see, that’s the beauty of it – because no one can just take it away, banks are more than happy to use it as collateral to hand you the cash for your real estate dreams. Now, here’s the real question: What do you do with that property to make it rain cash🤔? My first goal was simple – create a steady stream of cash flow, nothing too fancy, just a solid foundation. And that’s where it all began. When I discovered that I could snatch up real estate using other people’s money, the bank’s money, and then pay off that mortgage month after month, but still pocket a little extra from the rent – well, let me tell you, it was like hitting the jackpot. Wise words from Nåna🤲🏼 Let me share a short story with you. Sometimes the best inspiration can come from the most simplistic things in life. Yesterday, nåna was telling me to pull two big leaves off of our bismarckia tree (just google it, the leaves are massive) because they were already hanging down but I have been trying to pull those suckers down for the past 2 weekends and they just wouldn’t budge. They were still connected to the tree. I would even hang on it. LITERALLY. I kept telling her that I couldn’t pull them down because I’ve been trying for so long. I just can’t. Nåna was VERY persistent with me and told me to go and atleast TRY because she knows that it’ll come down. I disagreed, obviously but I turned around and said FINE…I’ll try but you’ll see that I can’t and it won’t come down. I walk over to the tree, yank one branch and BOOM, both leaves come crashing down🤯I turned around very slowly to look at my Nåna and of course, she’s smirking at me and laughing…. The point of this story is to show you that your words are extremely powerful and they control the outcome of your actions. If you say you can’t do something, you won’t be able to do it. Your mindset won’t allow you to.  If you say you CAN do something, your mind will focus on doing that thing and getting it done. There’s no obstacle in front of you. SO STOP SAYING YOU CAN’T & JUST TRY because you might surprise yourself😉 Say thank you to Nåna in the comments for being your inspiration today😎  DM me if you want to start making wi-fi money💸 #fypreels #reelsfyp #inspirationreels #motivationalreelsvideo #grandmawisdom #nana #viralreelsvideo #explorepagereels #reelsexplorepage #wisdomwednesday #explorepageready

original_post.description: See Caption⬇️ 🔥 Follow for more tips 📲🔁 Real estate crowdfunding: Real estate crowdfunding platforms allow individuals to pool their money together to invest in real estate projects. Investors can select the projects they want to invest in, and the platform handles all the legal and financial aspects of the investment. Real estate investment trusts (REITs): A REIT is a company that owns and manages real estate properties and pays dividends to its shareholders. Investing in a REIT allows individuals to invest in real estate without actually owning property. Wholesaling: Wholesaling involves finding a motivated seller who wants to sell their property quickly and then finding a buyer who is willing to purchase the property at a higher price. The wholesaler earns a profit by buying the property at a lower price and selling the contract to an end buyer (investor) at a higher price. Flipping houses: Most know that house flipping involves buying a property, renovating it, and then selling it for a profit. This can be done without a license, but it requires knowledge of the real estate market, construction, and renovation. This also takes Renting out a property: (This is my personal favorite) Renting out a property is a popular way to generate passive income from real estate whether it's short term or long term. In my personal opinion, in the right location. short term rentals and a lot more lucrative and passive when set up correctly. Short term rentals can be done without owning the property as well. Long term rentals can be done by purchasing a property with your own money and then renting it out to tenants, or using creative financing options like seller financing. This allows you to acquire the property with no money out of pocket and still receive income from it. posts_info.description: 🔐 How to flip a house, step-by-step 📝 Here’s a quick overview of how to flip a house, step-by-step. 1. Find a good deal 🏚️ I’ve done several videos on how to find the best deals, here is how I source deals myself:     * Wholesalers     * Multiple Listing Service (MLS)     * Direct Seller Marketing (Mailers, Cold-calling, door-knocking)     * Driving for Dollars 	Things to Consider:     * Price     * Condition     * Rehab Costs     * Timeline 2. Nail your After Repair Value, or ARV 💲 An experienced agent should run comps and account for overall market conditions such as:     * Days on Market (DOM) 📆      * Seasonality (Spring vs Winter) 🍃❄️      * Price Drops 📉     * Seller Concessions 🆓 3. Fund the deal 💵 A traditional bank won’t finance a fixer-upper and these distressed properties, so you’ll need to find a hard or private money lender Or close with your own funds (cash, HELOC) 4. Close on the property with a title or escrow company or an attorney depending on your state. ✍️ 5. Start Rehabbing 🛠️ Execution and timeline are key to ensure a profit. Ensure that you’re:     * Managing rehab budget     * Holding construction crew accountable     * Ordering materials with longer lead times ahead of schedule 6. List the property effectively     * Professional photos 📸       * Descriptive remarks that fully highlight the updates of the property 📝 7. Get Offers, go under contract and Sell the property 📑✍️ If mostly everything went correctly, you should be receiving a PROFIT! 💰 This isn’t comprehensive by any means 🚫, but gives you a rough overview of what to expect. 💡  #REALESTATE #realestateinvesring #fixandflip #realestateinvestor #millionairemindset#moneymoves #investingtips #howto #successtips #realestatetips #hustle #houseflipper #houseflipping  #cashbuyer #renovationproject #renovations #homerenovation - - - - - - - - - - - - - - - - - - - - - -  Follow @peakinvestingshow  - - - - - - - - - - - - - - - - - - - - - -  • Comment 📝 | Share 🔁 | Like ❤️ •

Househacking 🏡 We currently have a single family house with a basement mother-in-law (MIL) unit. We currently short-term rent our basement unit and we net between $1,500 - $2,000 per month. This amount increases during peak season (Winter) because we can charge more during ski season. There are many ways you can househack: short, medium or long-term rent based on your preferences and what the city allows.  Keep in mind that many cities require that you maintain owner occupancy of your residence in order to use any part of a single family house as a separate rentable unit. original_post.description: When was the last time that you were uncomfortable?🤔 Growth and discomfort go hand in hand🔄 Growing pains don’t stop when we’re keiki. You will experience a certain level of discomfort anytime there is a majah change or alteration within your life. When we look at this business, let me just say itʻs not for the faint of heart. In my opinion, REI is about 90% mental and effort, and 10% tactics and strategy. It may be messy, you may feel unconfident and discouraged, but you gotta be COMFORTABLE BEING UNCOMFORTABLE🗣️ I believe that there is a certain strength that is borne from doing things that are difficult. When you accomplish something that takes a lot out of you, it gives you a resiliency that you just can’t duplicate. When you look back at that mountain and realize that you have climbed it, you become fully aware of your own capabilities🗻. You realize that you are greater than the problems or circumstances that may unfold. We can’t control all of the things that happen to us; we can just control how we react to them. Because when it really comes down to it, tough times don’t last, but tough people do💪🏽 So I ask again, 💭when was the last time that you were uncomfortable? If you can’t answer this or don’t recall, then perhaps it is time to try something new. Maybe it is time for you to step out of your comfort zone and see just what you will become if you allow yourself, if only for a moment, to get comfortable with being uncomfortable. Mahalo kākou in advance for the likes, comments, and shares. Mahalo in advance for all da likes and comments. posts_info.description: Be proud of the work that you put out in world. Know the community youʻre impacting, be aware of the families youʻre helping🧱 When a project is handed off to you, donʻt just do a quick fix and hope for a money grab🙅🏽 Put thought and intention behind everything you do🧠❤️ When you get into the REI world, you spend all this time studying and learning. Youʻre grinding day in and day out doing research on certain properties, reviewing documents, estimating your operating expenses, and evaluating risks🤔 There's so much that you learn, but what cannot be taught from a book are your values📖 Your morals define who you are as an investor, and quite often than not, are influenced by those around you👀 Thatʻs why it is so important to surround yourself with those you admire and aspire to. Other investors who hold your values in the same regard. The words we use shape the way we think and feel. In Chinese, the word “wenti” means both “question” and problem”. Depending on how we translate it, it can evoke different feelings.  Understanding the context and purpose behind what is being said allows us to interpret it without attaching any meanings that may or may not be initially intended.  Sometimes we can be quick to assume, quick to react to our subjective biases. Viewing things with more neutrality allows us to step outside of the default frameworks we are so used to operating in.  #communication #nuance #becurious #positivemindset #languagelearning #chinesewords #mandarinchinese #learnchinese #perceptions #fyp #lostintranslation #questioning #expand #growthmindset #chineselearning #linguistics #powerofwords

original_post.description: 🏡Ever wondered about the difference between first lien position and second lien position in #RealEstateInvesting? Understanding these positions could be a game-changer for your #investment strategy. The first lien position is typically held by your #mortgage lender, having the highest priority on repayment if you default. It's generally considered safer, but may offer less return. The second lien position, on the other hand, is subordinate to the first. It's riskier, but could provide higher returns. This could be a second mortgage, home equity loan, or even a #RealEstateInvestment loan. Are you a safety-first investor in the first lien position or a high-risk high-reward player in the second lien position? Comment with your strategy below!👇 Want to learn more? Check our new blog post "Understanding Lien Positions in Real Estate Investing" at our website. (Link in bio)🔗 Remember, no matter your position, the right knowledge can lead to #FinancialSuccess. So why wait? Start learning today! 🚀 Share this post with a friend who's into #RealEstate. Let's all grow together! #RealEstateInvestor #PropertyInvestment #FinancialFreedom #LienPosition #MortgageLending #RiskManagement #RealEstateTips #Investing101 #InvestorMindset #RealEstateEducation And a question for you: Have you ever held a second lien position? BEFORE AND AFTER This is the first time that my business partners, @leuri and l, gut renovate a 1300 SF property. I'm not going to lie. It was not easy at all. There were a lot of things that came up while we were working. It was super stressful. But we had a very good team that helped us get through this incredible experience. It was a single-family home but we converted it into two units; the first unit, which has 3 bedrooms, and the second unit, which has one bedroom. We will rent both units and will make enough money to pay the mortgage and keep a good amount of cash flow. We purchased this property for $145k with a mortgage. We spent around $90k on getting the property gut renovated. Everything is new, even the roof. Four months from now, we will refinance this property to take all the equity out so we can keep buying more. This is like a monopoly game but in real life. Even though it's super stressful, I love it. And just to think that one day I will be able to live off that makes me go even harder. The reason why people providing all details is because I want everyone around me to learn the game the same way I'm learning it, so one day you can be financially free. I want to inspire you guys. Anything is possible. I want you to understand that I'm no different than you. I am just a regular person like you, and if I am doing it, I know you can do it as well. All you have to do is start. #realestate #realtor #investing #investor #goals #Billionairemindset #invesmentproperty #investorhabits #success #dreamer #dreambig #landlord

original_post.description: A series on what I would go back and say to myself in the first few years of business 🔥🥹🫶🏼 Holistically, this is how it works everywhere else in life: You have to invest something to GET something. 🔥 There are SMARTER STRATEGIES than others, and obviously do your research and USE DISCERNMENT. But across the board, with body, family, community and BRAND… You want something incredible? It’s gonna cost 💲 up front. Time, money, sweat equity, equipment, travel, heart. ♥️ My first few years in biz, I had about 60% good advice in my ears business - wise and 40% that paralyzed my growth, and made those first few years miserable. Plainly, I was scared of debt, expenses, or mistakes If I could go back and hug that version of me, Look her in her eyes, and hold her shoulders, I would say: For every million, Expect to invest up front a MINIMUM of $100,000. “Back then” me, might have choked on that number, but that’s why I said “a minimum.” My first year in business, I went $60k in debt for courses, classes, travel, business and product research. I thought $60,000 of debt was a big number. 😬 The thing was, I was hanging with a network marketing crew whose badge of honor was becoming debt free. 👀 PLAINLY, I have used debt 💸  Probably $400,000 worth, to leverage on the way to $3M in growth. Today, I understand that before a  BEFORE A TRANSFORMATION, A TRANSACTION must take place. 😎 I wish more people were more clean and clear about what real business success takes…  About profit margins,  Startup costs, GROWTH COSTS, And that debt isn’t your enemy. If a $30k investment could change your income bracket for the rest of your life, it’s kinda crazy not to do it, even if your use “other peoples money”. I would tell that girl to take as much credit as she was offered, drop the shame, and make some big moves. What was your biggest takeaway? original_post.description: 💸 Deposits keep leaving banks… why? When is the last time you looked at the interest earned on your savings account? You likely saw you were earning a fraction of a percent in interest. As rates have risen, so has the incentive for depositors to take their money out of low interest accounts and invest those funds at low risk into instruments yielding 4%+. So of the $80bln+ in funds that have left the banking system in the last month, some is likely due to fear of a banking crisis, and some is likely due to people simply deciding to put their money where it will generate a return. original_post.description: Asset vs. Liability: Choose Your Bank Wisely  Shift your mindset and break free from the cycle of endless work.  It’s time to understand the difference between assets and liabilities and make your money work for you. 💰 🏦 Choose wisely: When you spend, you’re “choosing your bank.” Don’t let your money be consumed. Invest in cashflowing assets like rentals or precious metals to grow your wealth and achieve financial independence. ⚖️ Assets put money in your pocket, while liabilities take money out. Focus on acquiring assets that generate income, so you’re not forever working for money. 💭 Expand your mind: Think like an investor. Learn about different investment avenues and make informed decisions. Knowledge empowers you to shape your financial destiny. 💞 Master money, don’t love it: True lovers of money endlessly chase it, working their lives away. Instead, master money, using it strategically to build wealth, stability, and freedom. 🚀 Start your journey: Embrace the distinction, choose your bank wisely, and think like an investor. Take control of your financial destiny and create a life of abundance. #stitch with @kaylacaneat If you have an IRA PLEASE make sure to review your account periodically.  Its important to keep an eye on your investments.  Make sure that the money that you are contributing is actually being invested into stocks, index funds, etc. Every time money is deposited to log into your account and make sure to buy the stocks, index funds, etc that you would like to own. OR you can set this up to happen automatically.   Also, if you own stocks that pay dividends...make sure that these dividends are being re-invested. You will have to log into your account and turn on this feature.  Once you do this...all future dividends will automatically be re-invested.  #irainvesting #retirementplanning #investingforbeginners #investingtips #investing101 #investingexplained #investingtok #investingtip #iraaccount #401kplan #retirementsavings #buildingwealth #howtoinvest #howtoinvestinstocks #howtoinvestforbeginners

Avoid this mistake ⬇️ Do not get that Car LEASE or LOAN until after you buy a property ‼️ Did you know that it cost approximately $600 per mo for every $100k borrowed mortgage amount these days? On the flip-side, for every $600 that you carry per month in debt, you are losing $100,000 in purchasing power 💥 Therefore if you have that car payment around $300 a month, that’s hurting you if you’re in the market to buy. A better approach, would be to buy your house, qualifying for the most possible, and then getting that car lease or loan after the fact. This way you can have your cake and eat it too 😊 But of course - make sure that owning both is affordable. Be smart 👍 Curious to know what you can afford? posts_info.description: What is Emotional Awareness 🔑  Y'all let's work on this one together. Practice becoming more aware of our emotions. Those jokers are running everything, seems like, in the background, and we do to even realize it half the time…🤷🏻‍♀️ Like when you're nervous, upset, anxious, fearful, intimidated, overwhelmed, sad, depressed, happy, excited, etc…  #1. #1n you 📍pinpoint the exact emotion you feel and give it a name? (This one freed me up on a lot of things… whew chileeee 🤦🏽‍♀️) #2. Ca#2you identify 🕵️‍♀️ the root cause of what is making you feel this way and explain it to yourself? (Self-questioning is a powerful tool 🛠) When we become 🧐 self-aware of what is happening on the inside and can IDENTIFY the name of a thing we can bring that thing into the light. As long as we remain unaware and unable to identify a thing, that thing remains 🎭 hidden from us and in the dark.  But if anything remains hidden and unknown to us, it may be the ☝🏽ONE thing that is hindering us from everything else.  It may be the ☝🏽ONE stumbling block standing in the way of your growth and success in a particular area.  It’s VITAL to explore, ask questions and identify what emotional barrier is standing in the way and holding things up.  It’s also a way to free yourself from it 🆓 Example: With Fear. We only remain captives of fear ONLY as long as we believe in what it says about us or the situation. But the Moment you step out and DO the thing you FEAR. Fear instantly vanishes and goes away. Just like that 🫰 What do you think? 🤔  Friend, Love n Hugs 🤗 It’s your growth season 💯 #comfo#comfortzoneh#faithg#changeyourlifede#leadersi#confidencet#growthmindsetti#emotionalawarenessg#courgequotesak#breakthroughawarness

posts_info.description: Tax Deeds explained: (this is not tax liens or redemption deeds! There is NO waiting periods with Deed sales) 💯 When someone owns a house, they still have to pay taxes on the land.  When they fail to pay their taxes; that land is then taken by the county and sold at an auction. Opening bid is typically only the back taxes owed, which is usually under $3000. 😳 Once You purchase these properties, they are immediately yours.  NO REDEMPTION PERIOD IN TAX DEED STATES. ✅ If your state is only a lien state or redemption deed state; you can still purchase in other deed states like FL (online auctions) you have 67 counties to choose from! All types of property can be purchased: lots, residential homes, commercial, mansion sec townhomes/condos etc. If you are someone that: ✅Has a little money saved up but aren’t sure what to do with it. ✅Wants to purchase real estate. ✅Create passive Income. ✅Establish Generational Wealth Then this is for you! #taxdeed #taxdeeds #taxdeedinvesting #taxdeedinvestor #taxdeedjade #taxdeedwolf #taxdeedwolfacademy #realestate #realestateinvesting #investor #taxdeedauction #floridainvestors #offmarketproperties #latinbussinessowner #latinarealestate #mompreneur #entrepreneur #airbnbhost #airbnbsuperhost #str #ltr #businessowner

In real estate, we invest countless hours into securing a deal. From thorough underwriting and comprehensive market surveys to crafting meticulous business plans, the journey is as rewarding as the destination. But here's the secret: every single deal we don't secure is far from a loss. It's an invaluable opportunity to learn. 📈 Each 'missed' deal grants us insights into diverse markets, hones our negotiation skills, and refines our strategies. We uncover the nuances of different neighborhoods, the ever-evolving demands of tenants, and the subtleties of local regulations. It's an education that money can't buy. 💡 So, let's remember that in the world of real estate, 'failure' is a stepping stone to success. It's a chance to level up, adapt, and emerge stronger. No Margin, No Ngutang, Supaya Invest Lebih Nyaman ✨ Ngomong2 soal lepas dari utang, tentu teman2 minjes udh tahu klu dlm investasi jajan syariah kita gak boleh "margin"...Alasan dr syariah sbrnnya krn ada utang berbunga disana yg mana unsur ribanya. Nah gmn jika seandainya suatu saat nanti ada fasilitas margin yg versi syariah (seandainya aja loh ya, krn minjes gak kepikiran juga pakai akad apa jg tuh kalau mau ada fasilitas margin di indo), kamu tergiur gak? Ah..gak boleh berandai2 yaa kagak ada manfaatnya.  Cuman ada yg menarik nih bahwa investor yg sukses justru gak ngutang lho... Kembali klu mau ingat kisah bestienya Warren si Rick Guerin yg jatuh "miskin" krn saham krn pakai ngutang "margin" dan "short selling" (btw jgn dibayangin miskin versi kamu ya, miskin versinya dia mah masih kaya jg buat kita 🤣)..dan ini pesan yg dihighlight Warren mengapa ngutang buat kita gak bisa bebas investasi.  Btw bkn berarti ngutang alias mencari pembiayaan syariah gak boleh, cmn minjes ngrasa "investasi" itu butuh kenyamanan, krn kamu punya target profit investasi sejelek2nya 15% pertahun, tp bkn berarti akan konsisten 15% ya..ada kalanya kamu untung tipis setipis helai rambut di tahun ini (curcol ceritanya) atau bahkan porto minus dalam nget nget (lah roller coster banget tuh) namun ditahun lain kamu bisa dptkan return jaaauuuh lebih tinggi shg secara jangka pjg porto kamu tumbuh.  Jika kamu terlilit utang & kewajiban lain2nya, plus investasi masih merah, biasanya psikologi manusia akan bermain nih. We've taken some big risks, but thankfully they've paid off.🙏 For example, last year (Aug 2021) we bought a dying assisted living property (9 bedrooms, 11 baths) with the house next door attached (3 bed, 2 bath) and went through the process of converting the main house into community rental space (technical term is a Rooming House: multiple rooms rented out with shared kitchen/living space). We updated most of it, went through city permitting to split off the other house (which we since sold) and are in the final stages of getting this main house officially approved (instead of temporary).🤞🙌🏼 Because I want to be more transparent on here so you can learn from me as well, let me show you how this ONE property has significantly increased our net worth + income by the numbers: 👉🏼 Purchased for $735K (30% down; refinanced our home for the downpayment) 👉🏼 Reno costs + furnishings: $65K 👉🏼 Sold house next door March 2022 for $350K + borrowed private money of $190K (had to pay out the existing loan attached, long story, but we own it free and clear now) 👉🏼 Being a commercial property, based on rents, existing property ARV now $1.1 million 🤯 TOTAL EQUITY MADE IN 1 YEAR = over $500K! It also cash flows around $5K/mon.😇 Just one property, one unique idea. Major money earned.🤑 We will likely sell it in the near future and place our earnings into a syndication fund which will produce over $8K/month in completely passive cash flow. This is the power of real estate when you do it right. #midtermrental #roominghouse #commercialrealestate  #rentalproperty #biggerpockets #investormindset #investorchick #realestateinvesting #realestatejourney #realestateinvestor #passiveincome #investortips

Some girls go browse Target when they need a "pick me up." I go look at real estate.😉🤩 I've been doing this kind of thing since I was in high school (ahem 20 years ago) so this is nothing new for me. But as I've shifted to sharing more about my love for real estate on here and my investor journey, I want to simply share what I'm learning, loving, and applying. So quick tip if you're looking at STR (short term rental) investing: go to some open houses, especially the luxury market to get furnishing ideas and find out what's popular right now. I saw a LOT of butlers pantries, modern boho vibes, and textures (that's always been "in"). Is being the tortoise good or bad? #comfortable #investing  Are you tired of chasing the latest trends and fads in the stock market? 😓 Do you want to invest your money wisely and securely for the long term? 🙌 If so, you might want to learn from the tortoise. 🐢 The tortoise is a symbol of patience, persistence, and prudence. It does not rush or panic, but moves steadily towards its goal. The tortoise knows that slow and steady wins the race. 🏆 In this video, we will show you how to be the tortoise in investing. 📺 We will explain the benefits of investing in trust funds, which are professionally managed portfolios of stocks, bonds, or other assets. Trust funds can offer you diversification, stability, and tax advantages. 💰 We will also share some tips on how to choose the best trust funds for your needs and goals. 🎯 By investing in trust funds, you can build a solid foundation for your retirement. 🏠 You can enjoy the peace of mind that comes from knowing that your money is working for you, even when you are not. 😊 You can also take advantage of the power of compounding, which means that your money grows faster over time as it earns interest on interest. 🔥 So, if you want to be the tortoise in investing, watch this video and learn how to invest in trust funds. 🙏 You will discover how to make smart and safe choices that will pay off in the long run. 💯 Remember, it’s not about how fast you go, but how far you go. My plan was to reduce personal debt against my home mortgage by taking on investment debt. 🏡 I sold both houses for $505,000 and $535,000, making a profit of $200k+ at the time. original_post.description: When a seller says they are not interested in selling their property, that is just the start of the conversation. In Seattle when I am prospecting, I am looking for small fixer upper houses (preferably with unfinished basements) on big lots with development potential. This means that even if the seller doesn’t want to sell the entire property there are multiple ways to still help them  depending on their situation. 🙌 At this house for example the owner wants to either sell the back lot or work together to develop the back lot and then keep it as a rental for their aging parents. 🙏🏻 In a situation where the owner isn’t ready to sell the whole property, I am able to help by buying the back lot and putting cash in their pocket or even by consulting and coordinating the development process to ensure things go smoothly. 🏝️ #seattle #dadu #adu #development #realestate #investor #realestareinvestor #building #rei #realestateinvesting #realestateagent #investing #realestatewholesaling #realestatetipsoftheday #realestateagenttips #investinyourself #investing101 #investingtips #investormindset #investor

posts_info.description: Had Jan Wanot on the Ian Love’s Real Estate Podcast to share his path to financial freedom. As he says “If you want to reach financial freedom with a 9-5 you better find youself a 5-9.” #investing #realestateinvesting #abundance #realestate #realestateinvestor #investor #financialfreedom

The first step is always the hardest. It took me over 2 years to save enough for my first property. I was making $55K a year working 60-70 hours a week in public accounting while sharing the bottom floor of a duplex with 2 roommates to save enough to put 10% down on my first place.  My first house was a bank owned single family home with a mother in law unit and second kitchen. The mortgage was $1,400 a month and I rented out the bottom unit for $1,200. I slowly added value over the next couple years by remodeling the bathrooms, doing some cosmetic updates and improving the landscaping. That allowed me to get a new appraisal, refinance and pull out $90,000 of equity. I used that $90,000 along with $50,000 I had saved by only paying $200/mo for mortgage to buy a 4 plex. From there I was able to continue finding ways to scale and none of that would have happened if I didn’t sacrifice up front to do what I needed to do to buy the first deal.  Takeaways  1. You have to be willing to sacrifice for a few years to get your expenses as low as possible and save as much of your income as possible to be able to invest and get in the real estate game. 2. Once you are ready to buy and have put in that work for a few years WHAT you buy is equally important. If you buy a single family home with no rental potential you are just hoping for the market to go up over time. If you buy a fixer upper and something with rental potential this allows you to scale because it helps you to keep your expenses very low so you can invest a higher percentage of your income instead of having it all go towards your mortgage. #investing #realestateinvesting #abundance #realestate #realestateinvestor #investor

It’s time to think like a smart business person with an investor mindset. That means setting yourself up for success first. Start with buying a house, and make sure it has a garage to park that car. Same goes for any other flashy toys you may be eyeing up, like boats or motorcycles. By prioritizing your investments and focusing on long-term goals, you’ll be able to escape the rat race and enjoy the fruits of your labor down the line. So, when that car temptation starts creeping in, just remember to hold off and call me instead. posts_info.description: Are you feeling stuck? The good news is that there’s a simple hack to get you moving in the right direction. It starts with a countdown: five, four, three, two, one, go. By taking a moment to count down, you can reprogram your mind to take immediate action and break out of your current funk. It works in all areas of life – whether you’re struggling to get out of bed on a cold morning, or you’re feeling stagnant in your business. This technique, popularized by Mel Robbins, simulates the countdown of a rocket ship, getting you ready to take off as soon as you hit one. So, whether you need to take the next step in your career, your finances, your family life, or your spiritual journey, start your countdown and get ready to blast off to new heights. . . . . #GetMoving #TakeActionNow #BreakOut #NewBeginnings #NextStep #ReachForTheStars #CountdownToSuccess #BlastOff #AchieveYourGoals #levelup

Let's face it, doing taxes is not enjoyable for anyone. However, there are ways to make the process less stressful and more organized. One tip that has helped many people is to get a credit card and make all business-related purchases on it. This way, you can easily keep track of expenses and organize them for tax season. Plus, if you choose a credit card that has reward points, you can actually benefit from making these purchases. For example, with a Capital One credit card, you can accumulate points for free travel. This makes the process of buying materials for your business feel like less of a burden and more like a smart financial decision. At the end of the year, simply print out your bank statement and all the information you need for taxes is right there. How to make money with Bitcoin and cryptocurrency investing: Making money in crypto requires research, preparation, and risk management. Here are some bullet points to guide you: 	✅1.	Education and Research: 	•	Learn blockchain fundamentals. 	•	Understand different cryptocurrencies and their use cases. 	•	Stay updated with industry news. 	✅2.	Choose a Reputable Exchange: 	•	Ensure security features are robust. 	•	Consider fees and user experience. 	✅3.	Investment Strategies: 	•	HODL: Buy and hold a cryptocurrency long-term. 	•	Trading: Engage in buying low and selling high on shorter timeframes. 	•	Staking: Lock up a certain amount of a cryptocurrency to support network operations in return for rewards. 	✅4.	Diversify Portfolio: 	•	Avoid putting all money into one asset. 	•	Consider various crypto categories like coins, tokens, and DeFi projects. 	✅5.	Security First: 	•	Use hardware wallets for significant amounts. 	•	Enable two-factor authentication. 	•	Never share private keys. 	✅6.	Participate in ICOs/IDOs/IEOs: (IF POSSIBLE, this is very difficult to find) 	•	Initial offerings can have potential for high returns. 	•	Thoroughly research the project and team behind it. 	✅7.	Engage in Yield Farming or Liquidity Mining: 	•	Supply crypto assets to a protocol to earn rewards. 	•	Be aware of associated risks and impermanent loss. 	✅8.	Be Wary of Hype and FOMO (Fear of Missing Out): 	•	Don’t make impulsive decisions. 	•	Always research before investing. 	✅9.	Stay Updated on Regulations: 	•	Know the legal implications of your crypto activities. 	•	Report and pay taxes appropriately. 	✅10.	Risk Management: 	•	Only invest what you can afford to lose. 	•	Set clear profit-taking and loss-cutting strategies. ⚠️Remember, the crypto market is volatile and speculative. Always do your due diligence and consider consulting with a financial advisor. 🕺🏻Follow for more #advice #crypto

You see the highs, not the many, many lows. You see the successes, not how many times I have fallen flat on my face to get there.  You see the shiny, sexy moments, not the dark nights of the soul curled up in a little ball.  That’s okay. Those things are real. Those moments are precious.  They get to be shared, remembered and celebrated.  Today I flew to Sydney to celebrate an achievement and massive milestone in my online business. Sounds epic right? However seconds before my name was called and I was due to accept an award in front of 200 people. I got a message from home…my grandfather had died. And whilst I was holding back the tears, I stood there, smiling, dancing like I didn’t have a care in the world.  Earlier today, a dear friend and team member in said business commented on how rewarding it must be to see our team, our vision and bank accounts grow.  What she didn’t see was all the late nights the tears, the sacrifices and the stress that it took to get there.  Now…don’t worry this post is by no means of pity party.  If anything let this be a reminder that what you see online is just a glimpse, a mere fraction of the whole experience.  And no matter how fun, glamorous, amazing someone’s life looks online, just know…their shit smells too.  So the next time you get knocked down by life, please remember success is nothing more and nothing less than just getting back up ONE MORE TIME than you get knocked down. Keep going you gorgeous specimen of a human.   As you were… X Y #instagramvsreality #overnightsuccess #success #successmindset #successmotivation #keepgoing

You’ve been lied to.  We’re led to believe that a job gives us financial security. The cold hard truth is, your employer doesn’t owe you anything. You can be made redundant at any time. Your so called financial security and safety going down the drain with it.  We’re told to invest in shares, stocks, bonds or even crypto, gold and silver. The reality however, is that you have no control whatsoever about the return on your investments. All you can ever do is sit there, fingers crossed 🤞🏽 and hope the market does what it was supposed to do.  We grow up, believing that we have to save our money. Tuck it safely away…at first in a piggy bank, later at a grown-up bank. But do you realise that in the current economic climate, your dollar will be worth a fifth (!) in buying power a year down the line.  A fifth!!  There’s only one thing that you can always count on to secure and stabilise and future proof your financial situation, and that my love is YOU!  When you invest in yourself, in a personal brand, in learning a new skill set and in your personal growth, you and you alone can secure your financial future l! You get behind the wheel and take matters into your own hands, sleeping soundly, knowing that you at any time can move those dials, shift those levers and create more wealth, not just in the short term, not just for tomorrow, but for generations to come.  Now that, that’s what I call financial security!  I so often hear people say ‘it’s just not the right time’, ‘I need to wait till my finances get a bit more stable’,  ‘until I have that job’ or  ‘until I have all my financial ducks in a row’ The truth -or at least my truth- is that those ducks don’t just fall in a row, they are carefully curated and placed there by your courage to go all in on you. Here are 25 savings tips that can help you to save money and improve your financial health: 1. Create a budget and stick to it. 2. Cook at home and avoid eating out as much as possible. 3. Use coupons and discounts to save money on purchases. 4. Take advantage of free activities and entertainment options. 5. Use public transportation instead of driving to save money on gas and parking. 6. Pay off high-interest debt as quickly as possible. 7. Set up automatic transfers to a savings account each month. 8. Cut back on subscriptions and memberships you don't use. 9. Use energy-efficient appliances and bulbs to reduce utility bills. 10. Buy generic brands instead of name brands to save money. 11. Take advantage of cashback and reward programs. 12. Use a credit card with no annual fee and pay off the balance each month. 13. Purchase items in bulk to save money in the long run. 14. Shop around for the best deals on insurance. 15. Avoid impulse purchases and stick to a shopping list. 16. Use a programmable thermostat to save on heating and cooling costs. 17. Screw a super detailed budget! 🙅‍♂️ Contrary to popular belief, you don’t need a super detailed budget to restrict your spending. Why? Because most people quit their budget after a couple months and let’s be honest, budgets are boring. 😴 That being said, I still think it’s valuable to track your cash flow (income vs. expenses) from previous months to gain clarity on your money. 📊 But here’s the fun part: I like planning my income, investments, savings and expenses ahead of time. 😁 For example, if your income is $5,000 per month, create a game plan on how to allocate that $5,000 over the next 12 months. posts_info.description: Seller Financing is a great tool! I’m an advocate for this strategy but before jumping into anything, make sure you weigh out your pros & cons. Here are some cons:  ▫️ Limited buyer protections: When considering seller financing, it’s important to be aware that there may be fewer regulations in place to protect home buyers, so thorough research is crucial.  ▫️Risk of foreclosure if seller doesn’t pay: In seller financing arrangements, if the seller fails to make their mortgage payments, the buyer could potentially face the risk of foreclosure, emphasizing the need for trust and reliability.  ▫️No home inspection/PMI can lead to overpayment: Without a mandatory home inspection or private mortgage insurance (PMI), buyers should exercise caution to avoid paying more than the property is worth, making thorough due diligence essential. #DueDiligence #PropertyValue ▫️Higher interest rates, larger down payment: Seller financing often involves higher interest rates and a larger down payment compared to traditional financing options, requiring careful consideration of financial commitments. ▫️Sellers face default risks: Sellers who offer financing carry the risk of the borrower defaulting on payments, highlighting the importance of evaluating the borrower’s financial capability and ensuring a secure payment arrangement.  #realestate #realestateinvesting #ownerfinancing

Let's imagine you're buying a house for $500,000, and instead of getting a loan from a bank, the person selling the house offers to lend you the money themselves. This is called seller financing. Here's how it could work: Let's say you agree to make a down payment of 20%, which is $100,000. The remaining amount you need to borrow from the seller is $400,000. You and the seller decide that you'll pay back the loan over a period of 10 years, which is 120 months. The interest rate on the loan is 5% per year. Now, to figure out your monthly payment, we need to take into account the loan amount and the interest rate. For the first month, your payment would be $5,000. Each month, you'll pay a part of the loan amount and a part of the interest. As you make your monthly payments, the amount you owe decreases, so the interest you pay also decreases over time. So, seller financing is when the person selling the house acts like a bank and offers you a loan to buy the house. You'll make monthly payments to them instead of a bank. The specific terms, like the down payment, interest rate, and loan duration, can be negotiated between you and the seller. #sellerfinancing #creativefinancing
