Some may seem simple to you but that’s because they are. The hard part is taking the action. 1. Discipline + Consistency: They are the key ingredients for success in any endeavor. They help to build good habits, maintain focus, and achieve long-term goals. Without these qualities, it’s difficult to make progress and see the desired outcomes. Discipline and consistency are essential for creating a solid foundation for success and growth. 2. Two minute rule : This is a productivity strategy that suggests if a task takes less than two minutes to complete, you should do it immediately. The idea is to tackle small tasks right away rather than adding them to a to-do list or letting them pile up. By following this rule, you can prevent small tasks from becoming larger and more time-consuming. It helps to reduce procrastination and keeps you on top of your responsibilities, ultimately improving productivity and efficiency. 3. Practice deep work: This means focusing without distraction on a demanding task. It requires dedicated, undisturbed time and can lead to increased productivity and high-quality output. (If you want a video explaining how to utilize deep work comment “Deep Work”)  4. Stick to a routine: A routine is important because it brings structure, consistency, and a sense of stability to your daily life. It helps establish good habits, reduce stress, and manage time effectively, leading to a healthier and more balanced lifestyle. Sometimes running your own online business can be overwhelming which is why your habits are so important. These have greatly increased my quality of life.  What habits help you with yours? Can see from his expression that he is very happy. We don’t know how tough their job are for today but it’s definitely a kind gesture to boast their happiness and can relax for a while. #kindness366

Kindness #61 Was at vivo city just now, saw 1 tourist trying to take photo of the other 2 tourists photo, so I walk towards them and ask if they want to take photo together. They said yes!!! They are so happy, very lovely ❤️ smile back. After I help them taking 3 photos, I ask them if they are ok for me to take a photo with them, they agree and very sporting, taken a very happy vibe photo.  So happy that I able to help them, they are so friendly. The only different I think is the skin colour, other then that they are very nice and fun people. Their vibe made me energize with happiness. 😁 Helping random people can be so fun and enjoyable. #kindness366

Kindness #50 Great reminder from Fb. I remember clearly that there is this China guy, (those 1 look you know type), he stand up from crowd MRT to let an old man to sit his seat. I thought he might be exiting the next stop or what……. No very far distance. I exit the MRT and he haven’t exit yet. 👏👏👏 appreciate for what he has done for others.  Sometime I don’t even remember what I eat yesterday but for kindness, I remember it even after 1 year, because it’s Made A Different. (M.A.D) #kindness366

Kindness #49 Last year dec, order this green drink from Starbucks, it’s having 1 for 1. I can’t drink so much, so I ordered and asked the lady behind me if she want it a not. I giving her free. She say she want to order other drink and tell me to offer the younger gal behind….. so I ask the younger girl behind, she said ok but ask me if she need to pay? Of course don’t need, it’s free for me, I just pass it to you as I can’t drink so much. She thank me for giving her the drink. I love ❤️ the feeling. It’s joyful to make one happy. Need not be friend, anyone. Even stranger. 😀 #kindness366

posts_info.description: Save this for later 👇 The Truth about getting rich while being young is not all about money. The internet allows us to make an income. We live in a different generation than our parents. All you need to do is create something working for you in the background. I’ve been there, I did it - multiple times. With Airbnb and now merging 2 businesses together. Your knowledge, experience, and ideas can all be transformed into income online or by utilizing platforms like Airbnb to generate this so-called “freedom” we keep searching for. It’s not easy, but it’s pretty rewarding when you don’t have to put 8 hours a day in just to pay rent and live for the weekends. It’s not rewarding when laws change and things you built are cut off overnight, either. But is money really the end goal? I don’t want to be 55 and then travel the world as I was doing. Or have bad knees to be playing golf or snowboarding and scuba diving. The journey and experience is better than any amount of money - but the $ is necessary. The future doesn’t exist. All you have is right now. Whether you’re 23 or 41, age doesn’t define your journey. Lay a brick each day and celebrate the small wins. 🧱 Share this with someone who needs a bit of motivation. 💪 Comment the word “COURSE” and you can be apart of our FREE weekly Zoom calls to build an automated business and community of entrepreneurs Inspiration @naval  @visualizevalue  @hormozi #RealEstateInvesting #InvestmentOpportunity #PropertyInvestment #WealthBuilding #InvestInMexico #BusinessResilience

🎯🚀 The results in your business are a direct result of your actions. ✅ Save this for later 🔢 Step 1️⃣: Everyone has an opinion. If it takes you a long time to explain your goals - it’s ok. You will be misunderstood until people start seeing your results. 🔢 Step 2️⃣: Take more risks… Sometimes opportunities are missed because you were comfortable. Don’t choose the easy route - because anything good never comes from something that was easy. It’s important not to make permanent decisions on temporary feelings. 🔢 Step 3️⃣: Data-Driven Decisions - If you find yourself saying the words “I think that… or this… or any “I” statement - you’re already damaging your business. Ditch the “I” statements. Making data-driven decisions means looking at data. Test it all - see what works - gather enough data - and adjust accordingly. This part is hard because it can be expensive upfront - in the long run, you’ll reap the benefits. 🔄 Stay consistent. 🔢 Step 4️⃣: Learn to say NO. This is my hardest one. Early in my career, I was a sponge, I loved to learn, network, socialize, and be the jack of all trades. I was the chess piece - and there’s nothing with that. As I learn to say NO - and be in control of what I am building, things have excelled exponentially with noticeable and tangible results. This is the hardest one by far for me. 🔢 Step 5️⃣: Ask for help. For years I felt lost trying to organize systems, processes, content, editing, everything. I didn’t know where to go or how many more YouTube videos I could watch. I joined an entrepreneurial group where the members have been successful in building large businesses - I asked them for help and got a mentor. 🔢 Step 6️⃣: Clean up your sh%t. Everything is connected through energy in life. Work on getting into a daily routine, automate daily mundane tasks, pay off debts, figure out your stress-causing issues - and clean em’ up - and surround yourself with decent friends and relationships. This will boost you. 💬 Comment “COURSE” below to join me on a Zoom call and help you build your business. 🌟 Inspiration: @thejordanpeh @hormozi @freest_man @timferriss

posts_info.description: **Investing in Growth Companies: Key Tips!** #InvestingTips #GrowthStocks #FinancialSuccess 1. **Robust Revenue Growth:** Look for companies with consistent, substantial revenue growth. This indicates a healthy demand for their products or services. 2. **Innovative Leadership:** Companies led by innovative, forward-thinking leaders are more likely to navigate industry changes and sustain growth. 3. **Scalable Business Model:** A growth company should have a scalable business model, allowing it to expand operations efficiently as demand increases. 4. **Market Potential:** Assess the size of the target market. A growth company should operate in an industry with significant growth potential. 5. **Financial Health:** While emphasizing growth, ensure the company maintains financial health. Strong balance sheets and manageable debt are crucial. 6. **Investment in Research & Development:** Companies investing in R&D are better positioned for long-term growth, as innovation often drives success. 7. **Competitive Advantage:** A sustainable competitive advantage, whether through technology, brand, or market positioning, is a key indicator of future growth. 8. **Customer Base Expansion:** Track how the company is expanding its customer base. A growing customer roster indicates increasing market penetration. 9. **Adaptability to Market Trends:** Successful growth companies adapt to changing market trends, showing flexibility and resilience. 10. **Earnings Growth:** Consistent earnings growth is a fundamental metric. Look for companies demonstrating a track record of profitability. Remember, thorough research is crucial before investing in any growth company. 🚀 #InvestmentTips #financialfreedom #InvestmentTips #FinancialFreedom #stockmarket #stockmarkets #stockmarketnews #stockmarketinvesting #indianstockmarket #stockmarketindia #stockmarketeducation #stockmarketcrash #stockmarkettips #stockmarketquotes #stockmarkettrader #pakistanstockmarket #stockmarketanalysis #stockmarketlab #stockmarketinvestor #stockmarketmemes #stockmarketca #stockmarketmindgames #woodstockmarket #stockmarketing #stockmarketmonitor #stockmarkettrading #stockmarketcourse #stockmarketupdate #usstockmarket

#Repost @the.moneyfox Investing is a way that you can build wealth. I don’t know about you, but I like the fact that I don’t have to keep putting the hours in at work to keep getting money in - it can passively grow in an investment account. There’s no risk free investment - and this isn’t advice - just an example of how you can look at different interest rates and how it can affect your money. This example is with 3% savings rate (which is better than it’s been in a while) & 10% investing. This is based on current savings rates, and return on a specific index fund historically (mine has been higher in this specific fund over the past couple years). There are no guarantees with investments but you can look back at history to see how things have performed in the past. This is just an example to illustrate the differences between saving and investing. And no I am not saying don’t save money 😅but I do personally think as part of a wealth building plan you should put your eggs in different baskets 🧺. Ideally we will all have lots of different baskets, but these things do take time. I’m all about learning about it and taking action, even if it’s a small step! As always, please like & share if you found this helpful 😀. Check out my other reels on investing all this week! Here’s something my mentor taught me when I was getting started in real estate: 👇 When investing in long-term rentals, there need to be two streams of money coming in…  One is the downstream, which is the money that covers the day to day expenses (that’s cash flow 💰).  And the other is upstream, which is the early retirement money that will make a person wealthy in 10 to 15 years from now (that’s appreciation and principal paydown). So, when phasing out of a 9 to 5, make sure to create both downstream and upstream money through real estate investing.  #realestateinvesting #wealthcreation #realestatecanada #rei #financialwealth #realestate

Bet you didn’t know this! Yes, higher interest rates aren’t all rainbows, but there are some good things! Besides the obvious of refinancing later… Hereare two unique ways to save even with a high rate: 1. Tax deductions: ✨ interest is tax deductible, meaning the higher your rate, the more you get back.  Let’s look at an example… The first year total interest you pay x your tax rate = the tax deduction for that year.  For an interest rate of 8% on a $400,000 loan the tax deduction is $7040 For an interest rate of 2.5% on a $400,000 loan the tax deduction is $2200 That’s a $4840 difference 🤯 Let’s look at the second way to save: High yield savings accounts ✨ You’ll want to search around to see who offers the most, but you can find accounts that are paying 4.5-5% + for interest.  If you already keep money in savings, you need to be earning $$$.  Comment “HIGH YIELD” and I will send you a few of my favorite high yield accounts.  Let’s save some extra money during these times!  📧Anfisher@sofi.org 📞704.369.7213 #highyield #highyieldsavings #highyieldsavingsaccount #taxdeductions #taxdeduction #taxdeductible

Calling all busy working mums 🚀 #workingmums  #schoolholidays  The summer holidays are approaching, but do no fear I have ya back girls ❤️ Here are 3 friendly tips, so you can have more time efficiently and enjoy workouts without getting overwhelmed! 🙌👊💥 No 1 Embrace the Power of Mini Workouts! 👍 Break your workouts into bite-sized chunks. Sneak in short bursts of activity throughout your day. Remember, even a 10-minute workout can make a difference! Find pockets of time, like during lunch breaks or while waiting for your kids’ activities, to squeeze in some exercise. Dancing while cooking or doing squats while brushing your teeth can add some fun to your daily routine and burn extra calories    No 2 Incorporate Family Fitness!  Involve your kids in your workouts. Make it a fun family activity by going for a bike ride, playing tag, or having a dance party. Take advantage of playgrounds or parks. While your kids play, you can squeeze in exercises like lunges, step-ups, or even use the monkey bars for strength training No 3 Focus on Efficient Workouts! Choose workouts that provide maximum results in a shorter time frame, such as super sets or circuit training. Opt for multi-joint exercises that work multiple muscle groups simultaneously, like squats, lunges, or push-ups.Incorporate dumbbells into your routine to add intensity without requiring much space or time. Remember, it’s about finding small ways to integrate physical activity into your daily life. Stay positive, be flexible, and celebrate every small victory on your fitness journey. Using a life insurance product that utilizes market indexes allows you to to experience market like returns without any risk of loss.  Why? Because your money isn’t directly invested in these indexes.  Instead, the insurance company invests your money in vehicles that generate guaranteed returns.  They then place options on the different indexes, and if those indexes increase, they exercise the option and credit your account. If the index decreases, they don’t exercise the option, and no interest is credited. However, there is no loss to your account as well.  In today’s market, risk and volatility are very high.  Insurance companies give you safety and security with these types of products. If the plan is designed correctly, you can also have liquidity and market like growth as well.  Insurance companies that have these products and Indexes like the S&P 500 can make this happen. "Leap of faith" in Investing. Howard Leibman, Co-founder & Partner at EVP (a Sydney-based, early-stage B2B software investor) talks about the investment process. His point on how part of the process is that taking a "leap of faith". No better way to put it! When you invest, you're not just buying a snapshot of the company as it is today. You're also betting on what it could be worth down the line. The economy's always changing, new tech comes along, laws change — all that can make the company's value go up or down. So, while you crunch the numbers, at the end of the day, you're also taking a leap into the unknown. It's a mix of hard facts (science) and that gut feeling (art). #Investing #BusinessValue #MarketDynamics #InvestorMindset #CareLaunch

🏡Ever wondered about the difference between first lien position and second lien position in #RealEstateInvesting? Understanding these positions could be a game-changer for your #investment strategy. The first lien position is typically held by your #mortgage lender, having the highest priority on repayment if you default. It's generally considered safer, but may offer less return. The second lien position, on the other hand, is subordinate to the first. It's riskier, but could provide higher returns. This could be a second mortgage, home equity loan, or even a #RealEstateInvestment loan. Are you a safety-first investor in the first lien position or a high-risk high-reward player in the second lien position? Comment with your strategy below!👇 Want to learn more? Check our new blog post "Understanding Lien Positions in Real Estate Investing" at our website. (Link in bio)🔗 Remember, no matter your position, the right knowledge can lead to #FinancialSuccess. So why wait? Start learning today! 🚀 Share this post with a friend who's into #RealEstate. It’s the eighth time in less than a year that the bank has hiked its trendsetting rate — a move that will make borrowing money more expensive. We’ve kept an eye on rising interest rates; and what we’re seeing is with the turn in the market we are seeing a decrease in purchase price. If you are able to run your numbers in a way that still allows you to cash flow during this market, image what your cash flow will look like after the market corrects itself in a couple years.  Real estate is a marathon friends, not a sprint 😃 so let’s hang in there and continue running your numbers. The market is finally normalizing and it’s a great time to buy (with the right purchase price). Don’t let the scary talk stop you from investing! Have the strategies in place to make sure you’re still bringing in the cash flow.
